DESCRIPTION: The attempted delivery of the ball from one player to another player on the same team. A player can use any part of their body (permitted in the laws of the game) to execute a pass. Event categorization includes open play passes, goal kicks, corners and free kicks played as passes. Crosses, keeper throws, and throw ins do not count as passes. outcome: 0 = Unsuccessful pass = pass did not find teammate | 1 = Successful pass
Name: Pase

DESCRIPTION: A pass attempt where the intended receiving player is called offside. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Pas? de offside

DESCRIPTION: An attempt by one player to dribble past an opponent. outcome: 0 = Unsuccessful - player lost possession or was tackled | 1 = Successful take on
Name: Dribling

DESCRIPTION: Indicates a foul has been committed. The event comes in pairs, with one for the team committing the foul (has outcome = 0) and another for the team fouled (outcome = 1).
Name: Fault

DESCRIPTION: When the ball has left the field of play for a goal kick or throw in. Does not include corners. (outcome = 0) and another for the team who will resume the match in possession (outcome = 1).
Name: Aut

DESCRIPTION: Indicates the ball has gone out of play for a corner kick. The event comes in pairs, with one for the team who have conceded the corner (outcome = 0) and another for the team who have won the corner (outcome = 1).
Name: Corner acordat

DESCRIPTION: A tackle is defined when a player connects with the ball in a legal, ground level challenge and successfully takes the ball away from the opposition player. The tackled player must be in controlled possession of the ball to be tackled by an opposition player. outcome = 1: tackling player's team gains possession or the ball goes out of play. outcome = 0: possession remains with the opponent.
Name: Tackle

DESCRIPTION: When a player intercepts any pass event between opposition players and prevents the ball reaching its target. Cannot be a clearance. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Interceptare

DESCRIPTION: A goalkeeper preventing the ball from entering the goal with any part of their body when facing an intentional attempt from an opposition player. Can also be an outfield player event with qualifierId 94 for blocked shot. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Salvare

DESCRIPTION:
Goalkeeper only event; goalkeeper attempts to catch an aerial ball. outcome:
                    0 = Keeper drops the ball after an attempted catch from a cross. They may then pick up the ball again and retain possession - this would be a separate event.
                    1 = Keeper catches the cross in one attempt, for example no drop.
Name: Minge prins?

DESCRIPTION: A defensive action when a player attempts to get the ball away from a dangerous zone on the pitch with no immediate target regarding a recipient for the ball. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Degajare

DESCRIPTION: A shot which goes/is projected to travel wide or over the goal. outcome: always set to 1
Name: ?ut pe lâng?

DESCRIPTION: A shot which directly hits the frame of the goal. outcome: always set to 1
Name: ?ut în bar?

DESCRIPTION: A shot which is saved by the goalkeeper or blocked by an opposition player. The player performing the event is the shooter. outcome: always set to 1
Name: ?ut ap?rat

DESCRIPTION: Attributing a goal to the goal scoring player. Given any contention around assigning a goal to an appropriate player, Opta applies its own rules and when applicable aligns decisions to the relevant official competition governing body. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Gol

DESCRIPTION: Cards are collected as yellow, second yellow or red card. Opta cross-checks the cards against the official sources to match the official statistics and aligns the collection unless there is recognition of a clear error. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Cartona?

DESCRIPTION: Player is substituted off. outcome: always set to 1

DESCRIPTION: Player comes on as a substitute. outcome: always set to 1

DESCRIPTION: Player is forced to leave the pitch due to injury and the team have no substitutions left. outcome: always set to 1

DESCRIPTION: Player comes back on the pitch. outcome: always set to 1

DESCRIPTION: When an outfield player has to replace the goalkeeper. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Juc?torul devine portar

DESCRIPTION: Goalkeeper becomes an outfield player. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Portarul devine juc?tor

DESCRIPTION: Change in playing conditions. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Schimbarea condi?iei

DESCRIPTION: Referee or linesman is replaced. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Schimbarea oficialului

Indicates that there has been a temporary stop in play

Goalkeeper only event; goalkeeper punches the ball.
                    outcome = 0 - the punch lands at an opposition player
                    outcome = 1 - the punch either lands at the goalkeeper's own team or goes out of play

DESCRIPTION: A player shows a good piece of skill on the ball, such as a step over or turn on the ball. outcome: always set to 1

DESCRIPTION: Event has been deleted - the event will remain as it was originally with the same event ID but will be present with the event typeId changed to 43. outcome: always set to 1
Name: Eveniment ?ters

DESCRIPTION:
Two players from opposing teams contest an aerial ball; these events come in pairs, one for each player, with the outcome indicating the success/failure of the aerial duel.
                    outcome = 0 - Player lost aerial duel
                    outcome = 1 - Player won aerial duel
Name: Duel aerian

DESCRIPTION:
A player unsuccessfully attempts to tackle an opponent as the opponent dribbles past them.
                    outcome: always set to 0 - a challenge by definition is unsuccessful and the player does not win the ball (winning the ball = would be a tackle, eg typeId 7).

DESCRIPTION:
A player takes a throw-in incorrectly, resulting in the throw being awarded to the other team. These events come in pairs; one for the player who commits the foul throw, another for the team that is then awarded the throw-in.
                    outcome = 0 - Player who conceded the foul throw
                    outcome = 1 - Player who won the foul throw
Name: Aruncare gre?it?

DESCRIPTION: An event which categorizes goalkeeper movement when facing a penalty taken. outcome: always set to 0

A player unsuccessfully controls the ball and loses possession (for example, makes a bad touch on the ball).
                    outcome = 0: the player attempted to control the ball and failed (lost possession).
                    outcome = 1: the ball simply hit the player unintentionally, and they made no attempt to control it.

                    Note - 17 June 2020: This is added 'post-match' which means it is only shown once the post-match analysis is complete. It is only added for some competitions. This is a legacy eventTypeId that has been reinstated.
